definitions.title: n.pr.m.
definitions.body: father of Shamgar Ju Jdg 3:31, Jdg 5:6, Anaq (Deinax, Kenaq);—v. also [[בֵּית עֲנוֹת]], [[עֲנׇת]] ´[[ב]] (cf. Tel Am. n. pr. Anati, Wkl:125, 43; As. n. pr. deae Anatu (Jastr:Rel. Bab. 153; hence) in Syria and Ph.—also Egypt—[[ענת]] (Muss-Arnolt:JBL xi (1892), 80 Pietschmann:Phön. 149 f. Hal:JAs. 7, x (1877), 374; xiii (1879), 208)).
